      <guid>http://localhost:1313/fiction/limited-invisibility/</guid>
      <description>&lt;style type=&#34;text/css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34;&gt;&#xA;body{background: #6E564A;}&#xA;body{color: #EEEEEE;}&#xA;img{margin-left: 5px;}&#xA;IMG.centered {&#xA;display: block;&#xA;margin-left: 5%;&#xA;margin-right: auto}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class = &#34;centered&#34;&#xA;src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/img/LimitedInvisibility-web.jpg&#34; width=90%&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div style=&#34;text-align: justify&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p style=&#34;text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;The Story&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The truck drove through the gate, and parked in a gravel parking lot between two windowless gray buildings. It was immediately surrounded by security guards. The driver got out and showed them her identification paperwork.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Back in the cargo compartment, where no one could see them, the passenger put on a special pair of boots and a vest covered with lenses and mirrors and complicated equipment. They flipped a switch&amp;mdash;and vanished.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
