    <item>
      <title>Roger and Deer 2</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/fiction/roger-and-deer-2/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Jan 2022 17:48:02 -0800</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/fiction/roger-and-deer-2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;style type=&#34;text/css&#34; rel=&#34;stylesheet&#34;&gt;&#xA;body{background: #6E564A;}&#xA;body{color: #EEEEEE;}&#xA;img{margin-left: 5px;}&#xA;IMG.centered {&#xA;display: block;&#xA;margin-left: 0%;&#xA;margin-right: auto}&#xA;&lt;/style&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class = &#34;centered&#34;&#xA;src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/img/RogerAndDeer2-web.jpg&#34; width=100%&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&#xA;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It was a quiet Saturday evening. Roger was sitting in the armchair doing a Sudoku puzzle, and Deer was laying on the floor reading.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;There was a gentle buzz from the servos in one of Deer&amp;rsquo;s arms as he turned the page. He hadn&amp;rsquo;t used to read all that much&amp;mdash;his old robotic arm didn&amp;rsquo;t have the dexterity to turn pages or operate an e-reader, so Roger had included &amp;lsquo;ability to turn pages&amp;rsquo; in the design specs for the new ones.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
